== Biography == The {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Moriya clan|qq=}} is believed to be descended from either {{ill|Moreya no Kami|ja|洩矢神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moreya no Kami|qq=}} or {{ill|Mononobe no Moriya|ja|物部守屋|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mononobe no Moriya|qq=}}, but this remains uncertain. Yorizane served under the {{ill|Suwa clan|ja|諏訪氏|1=Suwa clan|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa clan|qq=}}, the {{ill|Ōhori|ja|大祝|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōhori|qq=}} (chief priests) of Suwa Taisha, and frequently clashed with the {{ill|Negi|ja|禰宜|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Negi|qq=}} {{ill|tayū|ja|太夫|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/tayū|qq=}} Yajima Mitsukiyo. He was initially at a disadvantage but regained his position during the appointment of {{ill|Suwa Yoritaka|ja|諏訪頼高|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Yoritaka|qq=}} as Ōhori in {{ill|Tenbun 7|ja|天文7th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenbun 7|qq=}} (1538). Yorizane also opposed {{ill|Suwa Yorishige (Sengoku period)|ja|諏訪頼重 (戦国時代)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Yorishige (Sengoku period)|qq=}} regarding taxation on Suwa Taisha.
