== *Moriya Yorizane Shokutō* == A personal record written by Yorizane, comprising one volume, documents the rituals and management of Suwa Taisha from his father’s era. The surviving entries span from {{ill|Tenbun 11|ja|天文11th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenbun 11|qq=}} (1542) to {{ill|Tenbun 21|ja|天文21st year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenbun 21|qq=}} (1552). It includes key historical events, such as the birth of Yorishige’s heir in April 1542 and Yorishige’s death in July. While it initially covers the Takeda invasion of Suwa, later entries focus on shrine administration. The original manuscript was preserved by the Moriya family, and its text has been reproduced in collections such as the *{{ill|Shinano Shiryō Sōsho|ja|信濃史料叢書|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinano Shiryō Sōsho|qq=}}* and the *{{ill|Yamanashi Prefectural History|ja|山梨県史|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamanashi Prefectural History|qq=}}*.
== *Shinshi Ontō no Nikki* == A record of the shrine's annual rituals and notable events from {{ill|Kyōroku 1|ja|享禄元年|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyōroku 1|qq=}} (1528) to {{ill|Tenbun 23|ja|天文23rd year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenbun 23|qq=}} (1554). It describes significant occurrences, such as the peace negotiations between Takeda Nobutora and Suwa Hekiunsai at the Sakai River in 1535, and events leading to Takeda Shingen's invasion of Suwa. While the original manuscript has not been located, a copy made in {{ill|Bunka 14|ja|文化14th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunka 14|qq=}} (1817) has been used for reproductions in historical collections.
